He might not ever allow them to settle in, period.  Rome has more
resources if Persia got a sound defeat.

But who knows, he might and even if they did still revolt, I think he
would have a pretty good chance of defeating them.  Julian seems to
have been a decent enough general, even if trying to take Persia was
more than he could chew in OTL, he'd have been Emperor for almost 20
years before this TL *Battle of Adrianople, in his late-40's so he'd
be experienced yet still have energy,  and most important he would be
more secure in his power than the OTL Emperors were.  For one thing,
the army was pretty pagan, and would be more so in this TL, so the
Army would be pretty firmly behind him; on the whole I'd say he has a
good a chance at keeping the Goths from being a serious problem, one
